Created by Dr. Lili Zhang (2021-May-03)

Step1: Install Docker:
1) Go to Docker webpage and download Docker Desktop for Windows or MAC: Stable channel install it
2) Go to Docker hub https://hub.docker.com/ and create a Docker account
3) Open Docker Desktop 
4) Sign in at Docker desktop with your docker hub account 

Step2: Connect to Docker and Rstudio to Jiangyan’s server: 
1) start Docker and wait until it is running
2) Download the  image in docker hub from following website https://hub.docker.com/repository/docker/jiangyanyu/jyu_rstudio
 Copy the docker pull command (docker pull jiangyanyu/jyu_rstudio)
3) Open Powershell 
a) Paste the copied the docker pull command: docker pull jiangyanyu/jyu_rstudio
 Press Enter  
b) type in: docker run -p 8787:8787 -e ROOT=TRUE  -e USER=jyu -e PASSWORD=jyu jiangyanyu/jyu_rstudio:0.3 
 Press Enter  
4) open your browser and go to http://localhost:8787
Sign in to R studio using the username “jyu” and the password “jyu”
  You are now in the server of the Rstudio
Note: step 2 and 3a just need to be done once, step 3b need to be done every time
